-- Colombian Stock Movers: Pacific Rubiales, Canacol Energy Gain
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-10T18:00:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/colombian-stock-movers-pacific-rubiales-canacol-energy-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:35 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 2.3 percent to 13,227.75, while the
Colcap Index rose 1 percent to 1,615.01.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)   climbed 8.1 percent to 1,665
pesos, a four-month intraday high. The Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates fields in  Colombia  has jumped 41 percent since
Dec. 27, the day before saying in a statement that it completed
the drilling of an oil well in the Rancho Hermoso field and that
it is “fully financed” to carry out its 2012 plan of 14
exploration and 26 development wells.  Oil rose for the first time in four days on renewed concern
that Middle East tension will disrupt supply and as equities
advanced, raising economic optimism.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 7 percent,
the most in a month, to 39,500 pesos. The company said it
expects production growth of 15 to 35 percent and to spend $1.2
billion in 2012, according to a statement on the company’s
website yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
